ed commentary on several weekly TV talk-shows, including The McLaughlin Group and Inside Washington, views politics from a liberal perspective. He offers behind-the-scenes insight into what it takes to be a reporter, the foibles of political leaders and their times, not to mention talk-show hosts, as well as an occasional comment about Maryland.',22),(4456,'Gienapp, William E.','\"Abraham Lincoln and the Border States.\" <em>Journal of the Abraham Lincoln Association</em> 13 (1992): 13-46.','An analysis of Lincoln\'s policies in the border states, Maryland, Kentucky and Missouri, designed to prevent secession. After 1861, when each border state had pledged Union allegiance, Gienapp explores Lincoln\'s successes and failures in preserving or establishing loyal governments in each border state, fostering loyalty among its citizens, minimizing military occupation of these states, and ending slavery by voluntary state action.',22),(4457,'Gipe, George A.','\"A Moderator in Immoderate Times.\" <em>Maryland</em> 6 (Spring 1974): 26-29.','Sir Robert Eden.',22),(4458,'Gleissner, Richard A.','\"The Establishment of Royal Government in Maryland: A Study of Crown Policy and Provincial Politics.\" Ph.D. diss., University of Maryland, College Park, 1968.',NULL,22),(4459,'Gleissner, Richard A.','\"The Revolutionary Settlement of 1691 in Maryland.\" <em>Maryland Historical Magazine</em> 66 (1971): 405-419.',NULL,22),(4460,'Goldstein, Louis L.','\"Thomas Johnson and the Constitution.\" <em>Calvert Historian</em> 2 (October 1986): 15-24.',NULL,22),(4461,'Gonzales, Robert T.','\"Albert T. Blackwell, Jr.: Maryland\'s Newest Court of Appeals Judge.\"<em> Maryland Bar Journal</em> 20 (October 1987): 8-11.',NULL,22),(4462,'Gooden, Karen Lesla Williams.','<em>A Cross Borne: A Biography of Judge James Franklyn Bourne, Jr.</em> N.p.: Published by the author, 1993.',NULL,22),(4463,'Gordon, Joshua.','\"A Euclid-Turn: R. B. Construction Co. v. Jackson and the Zoning of Baltimore.\" <em>Maryland