rmation upon which this study is based.',22),(4776,'','<em>We the People. Montgomery County and the Constitution.</em> Rockville, MD: Montgomery County Historical Society, 1988.',NULL,22),(4777,'Weaver, Glenn.','\"Benjamin Franklin and the Pennsylvania Germans.\" <em>William and Mary Quarterly</em> 14 (1957): 536-559.',NULL,22),(4778,'Weichmann, Louis J.','<em>A True History of the Assassination of Abraham Lincoln and of the Conspiracy of 1865.</em> Edited by Floyd E. Risvold. New York: Alfred A. Knopf, 1975.','Weichmann was a native Baltimorean.',22),(4779,'Weiner, Arnold M.','\"Judge Sobeloff\'s Influence Upon Criminal Reform.\" <em>Maryland Law Review </em> 34, no. 4 (1974): 532-40.',NULL,22),(4780,'Welshko, Thomas G.','\"Stirring Up the Animals.\" <em>Menckeniana</em> 75 (Fall 1980): 51-58.','Political philosophy.',22),(4781,'Whealy, Mervin B.','\"\'The Revolution is not Over\': The Annapolis Convention of 1786.\" <em>Maryland Historical Magazine</em> 81 (Fall 1986): 228-40.','A study of the events that led to the Philadelphia convention to determine the purpose, meaning and consequences of revising the Articles of Confederation. A departure from traditional analysis that has more typically centered on the minds of the founding fathers, their economic interests, or the nature of politics before and after the American Revolution.',22),(4782,'Wheeler, William Bruce.','\"The Baltimore Jeffersonians, 1788-1800: A Profile of Intra-factional Conflict.\" <em>Maryland Historical Magazine</em> 66 (1971): 153-168.',NULL,22),(4783,'Whisman, Anne F.','\"Who Were Calvert County\'s Commissioners from the First?\" <em>Calvert Historian</em> 1 (April 1985): 1-7.',NULL,22),(14244,'Fenwick, Charles E., Sr.','\"A List of Alienations and Transfers in St. Mary\'s County from the Sixth day of June 1786 to the Seventh day of March 1829.\" <em>Chronicles of St. Mary\'s </em>, 28 (January 1980): 138-40; (February 1980): 150-52; (April 1980): 176; (Mary 1980): 187-88; (June 1980): 196; (