n into the future may literally be running out of time. An environmental columnist for the Baltimore <em>Sun</em> who lived on Smith Island in the late 1980s as an environmental educator with the Chesapeake Bay Foundation, Horton examines the water-related economy, traditionally based on oystering and crabbing, and the unique way of life that evolved in the relative isolation of the island communities. His book profiles the personalities of Smith Island, the work of men and women, the pervasive role of religion in island life, and social, economic, and environmental changes threatening the island\'s future.',NULL),(5134,'Hotchkiss, Horace L.','\"A Visit to Rose Hill in the 1850\'s.\" <em>Bulletin of the Historical Society of Cecil County</em> 61 (April 1992): 7-8.',NULL,25),(5135,'Howard, Florence Bayly DeWitt.','\"Beall and Edmonstons Discovery to Wheaton Regional Park: 1736-1994.\" <em>Montgomery County Story</em> 37 (November 1994): 309-20.',NULL,25),(5136,'Hoxie, John W.','\"Foxhunting at Belvidere Farm.\" <em>Chronicles of St. Mary\'s</em> 28 (June 1980): 189-96.',NULL,25),(5137,'Hurry, Silas D.','\"The 17th Century Tidewater, A Tentative Dietary Analysis,\" <em>Chronicles of St.</em> <em>Mary\'s</em> 26 (April 1978): 367-73.',NULL,25),(5138,'Hurst, Harold W.','\"The Maryland Gentry in Old Georgetown: 1783-1861.\" <em>Maryland Historical</em> <em>Magazine</em> 73 (March 1978): 1-12.',NULL,25),(5139,'Hutchins, Ailene W.','\"Ancient Graveyard at Gary\'s Chance.\" <em>Calvert Historian</em> 10 (Fall 1995): 27-36.',NULL,25),(5140,'','\"The Hyer-Sullivan Match.\" <em>Kent Shoreman</em> 9 (September 1974): 45-47.',NULL,NULL),(5141,'Jensen, Ann.','\"The Amish and their Market.\" <em>Annapolitan</em> 5 (October 1991): 36-39, 98-102.',NULL,25),(5142,'Jensen, Ann.','\"Christmas Past.\" <em>Annapolitan</em> 6 (November/December 1992): 19-22.',NULL,25),(5143,'Jensen, Ann.','\"The Colonial Thanksgiving.\" <em>Annapolis</em> 7 (November 1993): 70-73.',NULL,25),(5144,'Jensen,